H. No. 881 / 55 OG No. 23, 4216 (June 8, 1959)

[ REPUBLIC ACT NO. 2169, April 25, 1959 ]

AN ACT CREATING CERTAIN BARRIOS IN MUNICIPALITY OF TABANGO, PROVINCE LEYTE.

Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the Philippines in Congress assembled:

SECTION 1. The following sitios in the Municipality of Tabango, Province of Leyte, are constituted as barrios, to wit:

The sitios of Sumacab, Mina, Durabod, Lawis, Tipolo Tubig-Baho, So-oy and Payaw (Tabang-o side) to be known as the barrio of Inancatan;

The sitios of Colonia, Tigo, La Fortuna II, Cabato-an, and Danaw to be known as the barrio of Manlawa-an;

The sitios of Bahay-Dako, Hamorawon, Sabang, Palid Gamay, Hacienda Bough, Bulalakaw, Dina-ayan and Holipak to be known as the barrio of Gimarco;

The sitios of Tangohay, Ruscidelsa, Cocolay and Bagakay to be known as the barrio of Catmon;

The sitios of Banoyo, Cota, Palanog, Palanas, Bahay Camay, Batwan, Arimoso, Binanig, Manapaw and Panowayan to be known as the barrio of Gibacungan; and

The sitios of La Fortuna I, Tambis, Tag-abaka, Lugapak, Divisoria and Pagsa to be known as the barrio of Omaganhan.
